    <td class="rowodd" valign="top" width="2000">Regexp in&nbsp;&nbsp;substitution when getting module filenamewasn't anchored so it was turning X::Y::Z =&gt; X/Y/Z/Y/Z.pm not X/Y/Z/Z.pm<br><br>If module exists you start editing that rather than not checking if it exists and auto starting h2xs. This means you can create with vim X::Y::Z.pm then use !v to go back and you'll edit the module properly, added new var so you can be prompted before this happens if you want.</td>
